annotation.TEXT: Yeah, it actually is indeed a secret passage, but it's only traversable if the timer switch is active (must be a hidden timer gate there).
Almost there. You can see the gem I'm gunning for now. I just need to slip past a few more dudes without killing any of them (and without being killed myself).
BTW, if you hadn't gotten gem #1 yet, you can do so at this point. (It might be a bit faster to wait until now to get it, actually.)

Well, to begin with, I should collect the gem down there, which is pretty easy to get. Just hit the timer switch above, and then make your way to the gem within 12 seconds, which is way more than enough time.
Well, let's go back down and take a look at the bookcase I moved to the right so that I could reach the yellow switch...
Alright, that unlocked 5-7, but I'm not heading there yet. Instead... Hmm... I guess I'll go with 5-6, Giddy Library.
Hmm... Have I used Clown Mira yet? Well, whether I have or not, I'm using that one here.
Oh, and BTW, the enemies in this level do not give points, which is probably to prevent you from making them respawn over and over and farming them for insanely huge combos.
Happy Valentine's Day, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! So, let's see what the votes were this time...
Excellent! And, now that I've gotten this "pacifist" gem, I'm free to go on a killing spree!

Okay, for the next thing I want to do, let's hit the blue gate switch, and... oh, wait, I didn't want to hit that 1 button. I'll just hit it again to put it back. I actually want the 1 and 2 buttons set the same as when I went for the "pacifist" gem.
Now, by making gravity go to the right, this bookcase is no longer in the way of the yellow gate switch, so I can hit it now, and that'll let me get one of the gems above.
I could've also gotten that bookcase out of the way with the leftward gravity switch right there, but doing that would've screwed up something later.

Alright, for the final gem, I need the green gates open, and NOW is when I want to press the 1 button again, to return the 1 block back to its starting position. In addition, I want to hit the 2 button now.
Hyper combo! (5 kills, 7500 points.)

This is probably the easiest of this level's gems to get, because it doesn't matter what you do to the enemies on the way to it. There's no enemy-dependent gate guarding this gem, so you can kill/spare them as you desire.
Okay, now to begin with, let's press the 1 button once, but not the 2 button, and then go over and hit the yellow gate switch.
Oof. Yeah, I'm trying to go pacifist here, so I'd rather take a hit than accidentally kill something. Fortunately, since I'm using Daria, colliding with these guys deals less damage to me.
Beating that level would've also unlocked 5-7, if I hadn't already unlocked it from clearing 5-4.

Now, if you started the level by hitting the leftward gravity switch early on, the bookcase that I used to remotely hit the yellow gate switch would've been out of position, and I don't think gem #3 would've been collectable.
I think I have, so I'll just go with Robin Hood.
So, we have yet another unanimous level vote! And sure, I'll go with Cupid Daria here!
Okay, with the bats on this side all destroyed, let's go back down, and then go up the left side.
So, we do have this maze here, filled with various yellow, blue, and green gates, along with a 1 block and a 2 block, and you gotta figure out what combos let you get where you want to go.
This lets me access the upper part of the level earlier than normal, and is a necessary step to getting one of the remaining gems.
Oh, and I'll want the blue gate open in a moment, so may as well open it now.
Oh, and BTW, you need to have the yellow gates open, and the 1 button pressed, but not the 2 button, in order to go this way.
Oh, BTW, with the blue gates open, I could head to the exit this way if I wanted, but I'm not gonna finish the level now, of course.
Cool, made it with 101 seconds left, just before the "Hurry Up!" warning could happen.
Shooting that guy made the "click" sound of the no-kill gate closing, but I don't care about that now. Anyway, with the blue gate open, you can fly up here and get a bunch of coins.
Alright, just gotta deal with a couple more bats and carefully dodge some spikes, and then I can hit that upward gravity switch there.
Once up here, kill these bats, and hit the rightward gravity switch. And yes, that's the exit on the left, but I can't reach it with that bookcase in the way.
ERGH!!!
And, as you've probably surmised, this is the "kill-em-all" gem! Mwahaha! So, let's start off by murdering the duders up here...
Super combo! (4 hits)

Okay, so what if I were to use the gravity switches to make this bookcase move down, then left, then down again? Yeah... You might be seeing where I'm going with this.
No more reachable enemies up this way, but there is a duder behind the blue gate on the left that I just opened. Can I manage to include him in my current combo?
Easy as 3.14159. Just make sure you get that gem before you start fiddling with the gravity switches, or it might become uncollectable, depending on where the bookcases end up.

Well, it's kinda behind two different gates. The yellow gate must be open to reach the gem, obviously, but you can't even reach the yellow gate if the blue gate is closed. So, how do we solve this pickle?
Nice. Okay, that's enough comboing for the time being. Now, let's look at the level layout itself.
And now it's finally time to hit the leftward gravity switch here.
Obviously, don't accidentally hit any of the buttons while doing this, or it'll reset the bats, and you'll have to start the killing all over.
And now I just gotta go back up to finish the level!
Yeah, as you can see, killing even one duder closes that gate, but that doesn't matter now that I have the gem. And, I want to zap duders now to refill Daria's HP.
And... Have I used all of the Irvette costumes already?

In addition, there's a couple of new types of gates, which I'll explain eventually, but you can see a faded one over that gem there right now. (Oh, and Cupid Daria leaves hearts behind for a while, which is neat.)

However, I believe they'll still drop coins if you're using Irvette, so you can farm slightly that way, I guess. It's probably not worth the time spent to farm that way, though.
Okay, this level involves more gravity switches, but before I fiddle with any buttons, let's clear out the nearby enemies.
Okay, the final order of business now is to finish the level, of course, and that requires moving this bookcase up. So, we need to find an upward gravity switch.
Okay, to reach the other gems in the level, that yellow gate switch is necessary. However, one could become seemingly impossible to get if you don't know the "guide dang it" trick.
Alright, this unusually complex level is now done!
I will want the blue gate open later, though. Alright, let's continue downward...

And finally, go back up and make gravity flow downward once more.
Whoa, careful. I DO NOT want to hit that gravity switch right now.

Make sure the blue gate is open... Oh, wait! That's not actually necessary, because I can just hit the timer switch and go through that secret passage again. Yeah... The blue gate doesn't need to be open for this final ascent.
Oh, and I guess I may as well hit the 1 button while I'm here, too. No reason not to.

First, hit the rightward gravity switch up there, so that a bookcase below won't be in your way, then travel down to the bottom of the level.
Note that if you decided to be silly and hit the leftward gravity switch on your way up, the secret passage route would be blocked, but in that case, you could still take the blue gate route.
And, with the 1 button pressed, but not the 2 button, I'll eventually be able to make my way over to that gem there.
Oh, this level. Okay, this one is quite interesting.
Okay, before I fiddle with the buttons, let's get the coins that I can reach right now.
First of all, you DO NOT want to touch that leftward gravity button right now. Instead, hit the timer switch, and fly up to that area with the cracks in the wall above that I said looked suspicious.

BTW, the green gate switch and 1 button in the middle of the level do get used if you play the level normally, but with the route I'm using here (which I believe is required for gem #3), you can totally just ignore them.
Okay, I'm not "ERGH!!!"-ing hard enough, and this is wasting too much time. I'm gonna start over.

This is important, as the new gates depend on the enemies. This one here requires that all enemies be destroyed in order to open (that's why it was already open at first earlier, since there were no enemies yet).
I did a test run of this level on my 100% file before I started recording, and took notes of which buttons I wanted pressed for each of the different places I wanted to go.
And, we still have 5-B up here, so place your votes for either 5-7 (Steel Package) or 5-B (Oscillating Library)! Oh, and don't forget to vote on the costumes too!

1 vote for Cupid Daria on Valentine's Day, 0 votes for 5-6, 0 votes for 5-B, and 5 votes for 5-4!

There we go. Not bad. I will say that it IS possible to break the 8000 mark, as I have done so on my 100% file. (I was able to successfully "ERGH!!!" across that last jump without needing those gummy blocks.)
So, let's go up here, through the blue gate, and return gravity to its normal downward direction with this button.
Oh, and whenever you press any of the buttons in this level, the game spawns a bunch of enemies in the maze. And, if you kill any of them, then press a button, the slain one(s) respawn.
It slides that 1 block downward so that you can come up this way later, assuming the bookcase isn't in the way.
Actually, I do want to hit this blue gate switch now.

However, there's another gate that requires all enemies to still be alive. Kill even one of them, and it closes. But, if that happens, you can reset it by pressing any of the buttons below to respawn them, enabling you to try again.
Aha! That made the bookcase below land on the yellow gate switch while I was up here, allowing me to reach gem #3!
And, yep. I can easily exit the level this way, which I'll do later.
Alright, that's the second gem collected. But, for the last one...

However, Daria also has a downside, as her laser can one-shot most of these guys, I think. There may be a few that take two zaps to kill instead, but for the most part, one accidental zap will ruin my pacifist run.
